parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The premature deterioration of the wiring harness can cause electrical shorts, leading to sudden loss of power, unresponsiveness to accelerator input, and even fires, which can result in accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: smoke coming from the steering column

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ASR system can cause the vehicle to go into limp mode, reducing engine power and speed, which can lead to a loss of control and increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle goes into limp mode

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Drive train complications can cause vibrations in the vehicle, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents. Prolonged vibration can also cause premature wear on components, leading to further complications.
symptoms: The vehicle vibrates continuously when in gear
vibration felt through the steering wheel
unusual noises from the transmission or drivetrain.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine wiring harness can cause the vehicle to lose power and fail to accelerate, which can lead to accidents, especially when merging onto highways or crossing intersections.
symptoms: The vehicle experiences sudden loss of power
